# Pages Editor WYSIWYG (Inline Editing)

When creating or editing components that render Sitecore content, **always** enable Pages editor WYSIWYG by passing the `editable` prop to every field component from the Content SDK.

## Required Pattern

1. **Get editing state** in the component (or in each exported variant that renders fields):
   - Call `useSitecore()` from `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs`.
   - Derive: `const editable = page?.mode?.isEditing ?? false;`

2. **Pass `editable` to every SDK field component** used for content:
   - `<Text field={...} editable={editable} />`
   - `<RichText field={...} editable={editable} />`
   - `<Image field={...} editable={editable} />` (and `NextImage` / `ContentSdkImage` if used)
   - `<Link field={...} editable={editable}>...</Link>`

Without `editable={editable}`, fields render in the Pages editor but are **not** click-to-edit. The app already forces `page.mode.isEditing = true` when the page is opened from the editor (in `getStaticProps`); components must pass that through to the SDK components.

## ✅ Correct

```tsx
import { Text, Image, Link, useSitecore } from '@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs';

export const Default = (props: MyProps) => {
  const { page } = useSitecore();
  const editable = page?.mode?.isEditing ?? false;

  return (
    <section>
      <h2><Text field={props.fields.title} editable={editable} /></h2>
      <Image field={props.fields.photo} editable={editable} />
      <Link field={props.fields.cta} editable={editable}>Read more</Link>
    </section>
  );
};
```

## ❌ Incorrect (no WYSIWYG in Pages editor)

```tsx
<Text field={props.fields.title} />
<Image field={props.fields.photo} />
<Link field={props.fields.cta}>Read more</Link>
```

## Shared wrappers and child components

- If a **wrapper** (e.g. `FeaturesWrapper`) renders `Text`/`RichText`/`Image`/`Link`, it must call `useSitecore()`, set `editable`, and pass `editable` to those components.
- If a **child component** (e.g. `FeatureItem`) receives fields and renders SDK field components, pass `editable` in as a prop from the parent that has `useSitecore()`.

## Checklist for new or changed components

- [ ] Component (or each variant) uses `useSitecore()` and `editable = page?.mode?.isEditing ?? false`.
- [ ] Every `Text`, `RichText`, `Image`, and `Link` from `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs` receives `editable={editable}` (or the prop passed down).
